    ## Implementation Review
    
    ### Builder Layer (`mod.tsx`, `route-support.ts`, `types.ts`)
    
    **✅ `.withRouteContract` method (mod.tsx:378-383)**
    - Validates no prior route binding
    - Promotes type-state to `THasRoute = true`
    - Mirrors `.withRoute` API structure
    
    **✅ `promoteRouteContractConfig` (route-support.ts:47-83)**
    - Validates `$route` presence (throws `WI-12_MISSING_ROUTE_PATTERN` error)
    - Calls `bindRoutePattern(defineRouteContract(contract), $route)`
    - Promotes config to routed state
    
    **✅ `DefinePageRouteContractInput` type (types.ts:78-82)**
    ```typescript
    interface DefinePageRouteContractInput<TPathSchema, TSearchSchema> {
      $route?: string;
      pathSchema?: TPathSchema;
      searchSchema?: TSearchSchema;
    }
    ```
    
    ### Scanner Layer (`manifest-page-module.ts`)
    
    **✅ `scanPageModuleRouteBinding` (lines 1-60)**
    - Regex-based extraction of `.withRouteContract({...})` body
    - Distinguishes `.withRoute` vs `.withRouteContract`
    - Extracts inline contract body and optional `$route`
    
    **✅ `computePageModuleRewrite` (lines 62-200)**
    - Form A: Insert `$route: routePatterns.<key>.$route` as first field
    - Form C: Insert `.withRoute(routes.<key>.$route)` after `definePage()`
    - Form B: No-op (pre-bound in sidecar)
    - Idempotent (second rewrite returns unchanged content)
    - Emits warning when inline + sidecar coexist
    
    ### Discovery Layer (`manifest.ts`, `manifest-types.ts`)
    
    **✅ `discoverNetScriptRoutes` (lines 370-400)**
    - Scans page modules for `.withRouteContract` calls
    - Classifies as `'inline'` / `'sidecar'` / `'default'`
    - Extracts `inlineContractBody` for codegen
    - Excludes helper dirs (e.g., `routes/(_shared)/`)
    
    **✅ `pageModuleForm` field (manifest-types.ts:52)**
    ```typescript
    pageModuleForm?: 'inline' | 'sidecar' | 'default';
    inlineContractBody?: string;
    ```
    
    ### Integration Layer (`vite/vite.ts`)
    
    **✅ `pageModuleRouteBinding` option (lines 80-120)**
    ```typescript
    pageModuleRouteBinding?: boolean; // Default: true
    ```
    
    **✅ Lifecycle hook integration**
    - `init`: `runPageModuleBinding()` (sync, before first build)
    - `buildStart`: `runPageModuleBinding()` (async, before each build)
    - `configureServer`: `runPageModuleBinding()` in watch handler (debounced)
    
    **✅ Backward compatibility**
    - `discoverNetScriptRoutes` remains backward-compatible
    - `PageModuleRouteForm` type is `'inline' | 'sidecar' | 'default'`
    - Opt-out via `pageModuleRouteBinding: false`
    
